The problem is that your main code is not the same for integers as the other two types.

For integers you have this code:

```
            for (int i = 0; i &lt; arr.length; i++) {
                if (arr[i] &lt; 0) {
                    break;
                }
                dll.insertItem(arr[i]);
            } // int-input
```

You don&#39;t have this `break` for the other two types, and so those loops try to insert 10000(!) entries. As soon as the loop hits the default value a second time, your linked list implementation will complain that you&#39;re trying to insert that same default value twice.

I would change the logic to keep track of how many items were really read from the file (by making `i` not local to the loop, and using it to limit the above mentioned loop), or even better: use `ArrayList`.

Corrected code section with `ArrayList`:

```
        if (str.equals(&quot;i&quot;)) {
            System.out.println(&quot;int&quot;);
            List&lt;Integer&gt;arr = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(); // int-input
            try {
                Scanner sc = new Scanner(new File(fname));
                while (sc.hasNextInt()) {
                    arr.add(sc.nextInt());
                }
            } catch (FileNotFoundException e) {
                System.out.println(&quot;File not found: &quot; + fname);
                System.exit(1);
            }
            for (int value : arr) {
                dll.insertItem(value);
            }
        }

        else if (str.equals(&quot;s&quot;)) {
            System.out.println(&quot;string&quot;);
            List&lt;String&gt;arr = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
            try {
                Scanner sc = new Scanner(new File(fname));
                while (sc.hasNextLine()) {
                    arr.add(sc.nextLine());
                }
            } catch (FileNotFoundException e) {
                System.out.println(&quot;File not found: &quot; + fname);
                System.exit(1);
            }
            for (String value : arr) {
                dll_s.insertItem(value);
            }
        }

         else if (str.equals(&quot;d&quot;)) { // double input
            System.out.println(&quot;double&quot;);
            List&lt;Double&gt;arr = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
            try {
                Scanner sc = new Scanner(new File(fname));
                while (sc.hasNextDouble()) {
                    arr.add(sc.nextDouble());
                }
            } catch (FileNotFoundException e) {
                System.out.println(&quot;File not found: &quot; + fname);
                System.exit(1);
            }
            for (double value : arr) {
